# config/qa-pool/broker.conf — non-secret knobs for the in-yard QA credential broker.
#
# Copy to `broker.conf` in this folder (gitignored: it may name a host/yard path) to override
# the defaults below. The broker is OpenClaw's `qa/convex-credential-broker` (a self-hosted
# Convex app) run as ONE long-lived container on the yard's Docker. It hands a leased test-bot
# (SUT + driver + group) to each `--credential-source convex` worker, so N dev-agents lease
# DIFFERENT bots with no Telegram 409. Secrets and the bot-token pool never go here — the two
# broker role secrets live in `secrets.env`, the pool in `pool.jsonl` (both host-only).

# --- backend image (VERSION-SENSITIVE — read this) ---------------------------------
# The Convex self-hosted backend. ghcr.io publishes git-commit-hash tags + a moving :latest;
# there is NO semver tag matching the broker's pinned client (convex@1.35.1). The CLI (1.35.1,
# from the broker's package.json) and the backend must speak a compatible wire protocol, so for
# a reproducible yard PIN a commit-hash tag published around convex 1.35.1's release rather than
# relying on :latest. `yard qa-pool up` warns when this is left at :latest.
#   BACKEND_IMAGE=ghcr.io/get-convex/convex-backend:<commit-hash-tag>
BACKEND_IMAGE="${BACKEND_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/get-convex/convex-backend:latest}"

# Image used to run `npm install` + `npx convex deploy`/`env set` against the backend (a
# throwaway helper; runs on the yard's Docker with --network host so it reaches the loopback
# backend). Any Node 20/22 image works; the broker pins convex@1.35.1 itself.
DEPLOY_IMAGE="${DEPLOY_IMAGE:-node:22-bookworm-slim}"

# Where the broker project lives IN THE YARD: the `qa/convex-credential-broker` folder (holds
# convex.json + convex/*.ts). `up` COPIES it to the broker data root and deploys from the copy
# (so it never mutates an agent's live-bound workspace). Point it at a checkout in the yard,
# e.g. an agent's workspace: /srv/workspaces/<id>/vendor/openclaw/qa/convex-credential-broker
# Override per-run with: yard qa-pool up --source <yard-path>
# BROKER_SRC=""

# Loopback ports the backend publishes on the YARD (127.0.0.1 only — never the LAN).
#   CLOUD_PORT — Convex API/"cloud" origin; the CLI deploy + `convex env set` target this.
#   SITE_PORT  — Convex SITE origin; ALL HTTP actions (/qa-credentials/v1/*) are served here.
#                This is OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SITE_URL for the workers (acquire/heartbeat/release).
CLOUD_PORT="${CLOUD_PORT:-3210}"
SITE_PORT="${SITE_PORT:-3211}"

# Default credential `kind` for `seed`/`smoke`/`status` summaries. The telegram bot-driver lane
# leases `telegram` (payload: groupId + driverToken + sutToken). `telegram-user` (MTProto) is a
# separate, exclusive kind — seed it explicitly in pool.jsonl if you need it.
KIND="${KIND:-telegram}"

# Owner-id label the `smoke` self-test leases under (audit trace only).
OWNER_ID="${OWNER_ID:-yard-qa-pool-smoke}"
